Class DirectoryNodeStore<K extends java.io.Serializable,D extends java.io.Serializable>

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NodeStore<K,java.io.File,D>

    public class DirectoryNodeStore<K extends java.io.Serializable,D extends java.io.Serializable>
extends java.lang.Object
implements NodeStore<K,java.io.File,D>
    A trivial storage class that puts all nodes into a single directory with filenames represented by the hex-encoding of their key names.

      • generateKey

        public java.io.File generateKey(Node<K,java.io.File> node,
                                D d)
        Generate a key to store a node or data element. This key must be unique.
        Specified by:
        generateKey in interface NodeStore<K extends java.io.Serializable,java.io.File,D extends java.io.Serializable>
        Parameters:
        node - This is provided to implementations for some context. If generateKey is being called for the purposes of storing a user key, this will be null.
        d - If a key is being generated for a user key value, it will be passed along. This is most useful when things like a PagedList are adding a value, but the List API does not provide a way to specify a key.
